            <abstract>
                <p>An Amharic historiographical work that is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr7"/>,
                    where it is divided in two main parts, a Chronology and a
                    History of Ethiopia.
                    <persName ref="PRS3182ContiRo"/> states in a note in the same manuscript 
                    that according to a letter by
                    <persName ref="PRS4533Gasparin"/> from <date when="1940">1940</date>, the work
                    was written (<foreign xml:lang="it">‘scritto’</foreign>) by 
                    <persName role="author" ref="PRS14742Habtaw">‘Abtàu di Zeghie’</persName> (see   <bibl>
                        <ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1976Catalogue"/>
                        <citedRange unit="page">22–26</citedRange>
                    </bibl>). As Denis Nosnitsin pointed out, this work might be related to <persName
                        ref="PRS9347TayyaGa"/>’s <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1603Histor"/>
                    (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Tayya1987History"/></bibl>), but
                    more study is needed to situate it within twentieth-century Amharic historiographical
                    writings.</p>
            </abstract>
